The paper deals with the maximum matching problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The focus is on the oblivious setting, where the edge set of the graph is unknown to the algorithm and edges are revealed upon probing. This suggests that the paper is likely to be in the area of data structures (cs.DS) or graph theory (cs.GT). The use of approximation algorithms and analysis of their performance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of information theory techniques to analyze the performance of the algorithm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
